This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the development of a communication protocol between agents in a referential game. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of machine learning techniques to train the agents. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the development of a learning algorithm for the agents. The use of images and textual descriptions suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.SD (Sound).
